  "title": "feat(templates): allow Fragment as root",
  "body": "<!--\r\n  Thanks for submitting a pull request!\r\n  Please provide enough information so that others can review your pull request.\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Summary**\r\n\r\n[FX-2735](https://algolia.atlassian.net/browse/FX-2735)\r\n\r\n**Result**\r\n\r\nSettled with a `fragment` string after all, allowing a component is trickier to type because of `defaultProps`, and that's technically not what we want.\r\n\r\nOne problem is that since we still have Hogan templates and Fragment does not allow `dangerouslySetInnerHTML`, we need a workaround for still supporting them. \r\nI came up with a component that mounts an empty `div` and immediately sets `outerHTML` with the template's output. Of course this will no longer be necessary once we drop Hogan support.\r\n\n\n[FX-2735]: https://algolia.atlassian.net/browse/FX-2735?atlOrigin=eyJpIjoiNWRkNTljNzYxNjVmNDY3MDlhMDU5Y2ZhYzA5YTRkZjUiLCJwIjoiZ2l0aHViLWNvbS1KU1cifQ",
